## What is a server?

A server is a computer that provides services and resources to clients over a network.

Role of the domain name

It translates a human-readable name (www.foobar.com) into an IP address.

What DNS record is www?

A Record

because it points to IPv4 address 8.8.8.8

Role of Nginx

Receives HTTP requests.

Serves static files.

Forwards dynamic requests to the application server.

Role of Application Server

Runs the application code and processes user requests.

Role of Database

Stores and retrieves application data.

Communication

Uses

HTTP/HTTPS over TCP/IP

Problems
Single Point of Failure (one server)
